# Pharos — environment variables (template)
#
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in real values for local dev.
# In CI, values come from GitHub Actions repository secrets, never from a
# committed file.
#
# SAFETY RULES
# 1. Never commit .env.  .gitignore catches .env, .env.*, *.env and
#    dashboard/.env*.  The pre-commit hook rejects AIza... literals
#    (Google API key prefix) and sk-ant-... literals (legacy Anthropic,
#    kept as a defensive layer).
# 2. GEMINI_API_KEY is a server-only secret. Do NOT prefix it with
#    NEXT_PUBLIC_ — Next.js publishes NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars to the browser
#    bundle and the key would leak. AI summaries run inside the GitHub
#    Actions Python pipeline (see CLAUDE.md §10), never from the frontend.
# 3. If a key ever does leak, rotate it at the provider console (OpenFDA /
#    Google AI Studio) — that invalidates the old value immediately.

OPENFDA_API_KEY=your_key_here
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
DB_PATH=db/pharos.db
